This is a great opportunity for somebody who wants to get in on the action of a well-funded, fast-growing company in their 4th (and so far best) year of doing business. We are looking for talent to help us take the company to the next level in the live entertainment industry.</p>
<p>
We have an opening for an entry-level position ideally suited to a new graduate who perhaps doesn&#39;t have a lot of work experience, but is smart, hardworking, and eager to join a team environment. This position has historically been a stepping stone to more responsibilities if you earn them. We are looking for somebody who wants to get in and grow with the company. As a Data Specialist you will be doing Internet research, learning how to run projects, and honing all sorts of skills that you can apply to your career. Speed, accuracy, and problem-solving skills are very critical to this position, as is the endurance for repetitive work too. Most important is working gracefully in a team of specialists with deadlines to hit.</p>
<p>
If you&#39;re someone who&#39;s detail oriented and loves solving problems, then you&#39;d fit in well here. This is such a big part of the job, in fact, that before we see your resume, we have a few questions for you. If the idea of doing this sounds unappealing, then you probably aren&#39;t a good fit for the position. Also: we delete any resumes right away that don&#39;t answer the questions, so you would be wasting your time if you just attach a resume and send.</p>
