<strong>The Position</strong><br />
Reporting to the Director of Operations, the Inventory Specialist position plays a critical role to the success of ScoreBig.&nbsp; The role consists of acquiring and managing ticket inventory for various live events across the country in order to meet customer demand, and build case studies around ticket sales, pricing and projected volume of sales.</p>
<p>
<strong>Key Responsibilities Include:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Identify customer demand for low inventory events</li>
<li>
Acquire ticket inventory for low inventory events from a variety of sources</li>
<li>
Work with Marketing team to promote inventory</li>
<li>
Work with Pricing team to properly price inventory</li>
<li>
Create reports, recaps, and case studies</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Experience:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree</li>
<li>
1-3 years professional sales experience, marketing or analytics experience</li>
<li>
Previous experience in the ticketing/entertainment industry preferred, but not required</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Skills &amp; Personal Characteristics:</strong></p>
<ul>
