			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Founded in 2009, ScoreBig is a venture-backed e-commerce company building the first, opaque channel specifically for the liquidation and sale of &ldquo;undersold&rdquo; ticket inventory in the $26B live-event ticket category.&nbsp; The Company has been founded by high performance entrepreneurs with a proven track record in sports, ticketing, e-commerce and entertainment industries.&nbsp; The founding executives have attracted senior executives from leading technology and ticketing related industries.&nbsp; They have completed three very successful funding rounds from industry leading venture capital firms and have attracted a world class advisory group. The company is currently experiencing rapid growth and transitioning from its early stage phase to a high growth enterprise.</p>
<p>
Manager of Merchandising<br />
The Manager of Merchandising will be responsible for creating a procedure that allows the company to acquire and manage ticket inventory effectively.&nbsp; Develop and implement analytical methods on inventory assortment, promotions, and visual merchandising to improve business performance.&nbsp;<br />
Responsibilities include the following:</p>
<ol>
<li>
Conduct secondary research on Sports, Theatre, and Music events.&nbsp; Compile inventory availability data to identify inventory benchmarks.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Define assortment breadth and depth goals in accordance to ScoreBig&rsquo;s sales and inventory strategy. Actively review inventory gaps and set inventory acquisition priorities based on financial implications.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Develop analytical methods to optimize visual merchandising.&nbsp; Work closely with Product Team to identify opportunities, create, and implement solutions in regards to product presentation and space usage.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Establish analytical process to review inventory sales performance.&nbsp; Identify specific sales or margin opportunities and work with marketing team to execute product promotions.&nbsp; Drive the process to evaluate promotional effectiveness and optimize promotion product selection.</li>
<li>
Development of inventory monitoring reports.&nbsp; Work with technology team to develop tools that supports all merchandising needs.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>
<p>
The successful candidate will have</p>
<ol>
<li>
An academic background in mathematics, economics or a suitable quantitative discipline.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
<li>
3 to 5 years of relevant experience in business modeling and management, with extensive experience in quantitative analytical model development and implementation.</li>
<li>
Consumer retail experience in the area of merchandising or pricing is required.</li>
<li>
Strong MS Excel skills, statistical software exposure, SQL experience is a plus.</li>
<li>
Strong verbal and written communication skills</li>
<li>
Entrepreneurial drive and demonstrated ability to achieve stretch goals in an innovative and fast paced environment</li>
<li>
Distinctive problem solving, organizational and analytical skills </li>
</ol>
